begun in the 1920s but abandoned in the 1970s that was designed to create a 
chance for blacks to worship together at Easter. Planners of this year's event, 
the Val Verde Civic Assn., directed the service and community breakfast 
afterward toward a broader audience. DAVID BOHRER / Los Angeles Times 
</P>
