<HEADLINE>
<P>
1,300 SIMI VALLEY HOMES LOSE POWER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
About 1,300 customers in an area of northeast Simi Valley were without 
electricity for about 1 1/2 hours late Sunday afternoon and another 400 were 
without power for even longer as Southern California Edison workers hunted for 
the source of the outage, a spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
Company spokesman David Barron said the outage occurred about 5:25 p.m. Power 
was rerouted, restoring service to most of the homes by 6:50 p.m. Several hours 
later electricity was still off for the remaining customers. 
</P>
<P>
The boundaries of the area affected by the outage were Cochran Street on the 
north, Kuehner Drive on the east, Los Angeles Avenue on the south and Stow 
Street on the west. 
</P>
