<TEXT>
<P>
Baseball officials have reconsidered plans to sell its official statistics to a 
Las Vegas computer firm that reportedly provides information to gamblers, a 
spokesman for the commissioner's office said. 
</P>
<P>
Ed Durso, senior vice president for major league baseball, issued a statement 
in which he said advertisements by Computer Sports World offering the 
statistics with baseball's blessings were premature. 
</P>
<P>
"Negotiations between major league baseball and Computer Sports World were not 
concluded," Durso said. "We have determined not to move forward." 
