<TEXT>
<P>
A Silver Spring, Md., man who received what was believed to be the nation's 
first successful heart-pancreas transplant, could be out of the hospital in a 
few weeks, hospital officials said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Barry Katz, 45, a senior scientist for the Strategic Defense Initiative 
program, was a diabetic whose heart had been severely damaged by the disease. 
Doctors said they decided that because of Katz's condition, complications would 
result if only his heart were replaced. 
