</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Checks Go to Farmers: More than $18 million was mailed to 6,860 farmers in 10 
states who settled a legal dispute with Chubb Corp. over crop insurance 
applications rejected during the 1988 drought. Lawrence Kane Jr., a Cincinnati 
lawyer who was appointed by U.S. District Judge Carl Rubin last fall to oversee 
the payments, said the farmers should be mailed the remaining 50% of their 
settlement payments by late April. Kane said he and his staff are still trying 
to resolve objections by about 930 farmers who oppose the $36.6-million 
settlement with Chubb Corp., based in Warren, N.J., and its insurance 
subsidiaries. The class-action case involves 7,484 farmers in Illinois, Iowa, 
Ohio, Kentucky, Indiana, Tennessee, Minnesota, Michigan, Missouri and 
Wisconsin. 
