NATION; 
</P>
<P>
MUDSLIDE CLOSES ROAD TO UTAH PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CEDAR CITY, Utah 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A massive mudslide closed the main road to Cedar Breaks National Monument and 
stripped off a half-mile section of pavement, and it continued to ooze downhill 
today, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The slide, roughly half a mile long and half a mile wide, sent mud and boulders 
cascading across State Road 14 sometime during the night and was discovered 
this morning, said Utah Department of Transportation spokesman Kim Morris. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported. The highway had been heavily traveled during the 
Easter weekend, the Utah Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
