<TEXT>
<P>
The Atlanta Braves today released utility infielder Paul Runge and draftee Matt 
Stark and sent six other players to the minor leagues, lowering their roster to 
28. Runge, a three-year veteran, batted .211 in 52 games with the Braves last 
season. Stark, a catcher, was drafted from the Toronto Blue Jays' organization 
during the winter baseball meetings for $50,000. 
</P>
