<P>
33 ARRESTED IN FLA. MULTIMILLION-DOLLAR SPORTS BETTING RING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
TALLAHASSEE, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At least 33 people have been arrested in central Florida in connection with a 
multimillion-dollar interstate sports betting ring, state and federal officials 
announced today. 
</P>
<P>
The Louisville, Ky.,-based operation accepted bets nationwide on college and 
professional basketball, football and baseball in addition to horse racing. 
</P>
<P>
Phone taps were used in the investigation. 
</P>
<P>
"We've got calls where thousands were bet by one person on one game," said Don 
Marblestone, assistant statewide prosecutor. "We're not talking people betting 
10, 20, 30 bucks." 
</P>
