SUMPTER, ROSE SIGN WITH CLIPPERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Forward-center Barry Sumpter and guard Bob Rose signed 10-day contracts with 
the Los Angeles Clippers today. 
</P>
<P>
The roster openings were created Sunday when the Clippers released reserve 
center Greg Kite and placed swing man Reggie Williams, who has a sprained 
thumb, on the injured list. 
</P>
<P>
Sumpter, 23, played the 1988-89 season with the Quad City Thunder of the 
Continental Basketball Assn.. The 6-foot-11 Sumpter, who attended Austin Peay, 
averaged 8.8 points and 11.1 rebounds in 54 games with the Thunder. 
</P>
<P>
Rose, 24, played the 1988-89 season with the Wichita Falls Texans of the CBA. 
The 6-5 Rose, who played college ball at George Mason, averaged 22.2 points and 
8.6 rebounds in 52 games with the Texans. 
</P>
</TEXT>
